I"/<p>As seen <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/24102498/escaping-double-curly-braces-inside-a-markdown-code-block-in-jekyll">here</a></p>

<p>If you use double curly braces in code blocks in markdown with Jekyll. They just wonâ€™t show up.</p>

<p>Enclosed the code block in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">raw</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">endraw</code> tags.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>{% raw %}

{% raw %}
{% some code here %}
{% endraw %}

{% endraw %}
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Adding a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">JavaScript</code> code block also causes Reader View (for example in Safari mobile) to misbehave.</p>

